OL,3,C'That ship saved our lives': John
OL,4,CHeys' SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,F"They missed their families you see
OL,7,Fand I, strangely enough, had blonde
OL,8,Fhair in those days and I suppose I
OL,9,Flooked like a little German boy."
OL,11,FAfter more than four years of
OL,12,FOccupation, Jersey's supplies dwindled
OL,13,Fas the German strategy to starve
OL,14,FBritain into submission took hold.
OL,16,FJohn remembers trying to steal food
OL,17,Ffrom the Germans, explaining: "Every
OL,18,Fmorning four horses with a big
OL,19,Fcarriage would go by, carrying bread
OL,20,Fand we could smell the bread.
