OL,3,C'That ship saved our lives': John
OL,4,CHeys' SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,F"We would hide in the hedge and when
OL,7,Fit went by we would come out and try
OL,8,Fto get up the tailboard to get to the
OL,9,Fbread.
OL,11,F"But the Germans knew what was going
OL,12,Fon, and they had a whip that they
OL,13,Fflicked back to us on the tailboard
OL,14,Fand it would knock us off.
OL,16,F"We never did get to the bread but we
OL,17,Fcould smell it."
