OL,3,C'That ship saved our lives': John
OL,4,CHeys' SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,F"The thing that I remember most is the
OL,7,Fsmell of it. That lovely smell we had
OL,8,Fnever smelt before and to eat it - to
OL,9,Ftaste it - was just tremendous and we
OL,10,Fcouldn't wait for the next Red Cross
OL,11,Fparcel to arrive."
OL,13,FThis first voyage of Red Cross
OL,14,Fsupplies brought more than 100,000
OL,15,Fparcels to the islands. They included
OL,16,Fprunes, tinned meat, soap, and
OL,17,Fpowdered milk, known as KLIM.
